In the limit $m_{a,b}\rightarrow 0$ with $t_{\beta}=1$ and $t_{\varphi,i}=\frac{m^2_{n_i}}{m^2_{\varphi}}$, the contributions from the charged Higgs bosons $C^{\varphi}_{L,R}$ have the following forms:
(C7)$$\begin{eqnarray}
\frac{C^{\varphi}_L}{m_a}= \frac{C^{\varphi}_R}{m_b}=- \frac{g^2e}{32\pi^2 m_W^2} f_{s}(t_{\varphi,i}),\quad f_{s}(t) \equiv \frac{t\left[7 -12t -3 t^2 +8t^3 -6t\left( -2+3t \right)\ln t \right] }{12 \left(t-1\right)^4}. \end{eqnarray}$$
